parameters: I feel a strong sense of oppression from the northern passage...

……It's quite strong... I feel like it's better to avoid passing through
there.

……What should we do? There seem to be dangerous enemies around, but
should we fight them as we are? It seems better to take a detour
though.

The enemies stood in the way, guarding the stairs leading to the
depths!
The giant Frosleen individual looks at us with a wicked smile...
There is a Frosleen who doesn't seem hostile...
I'm sorry... I'm not quite sure what you're saying...
There is a Frosleen priest who doesn't seem to have any hostility...

Right now, many tribes are gathering here. Among them, there are also
tribes that hold hostility towards humans.

Daga, the will of the selected high chiefs from each tribe is
absolute. It's best to proceed with caution until the war breaks out.

Frosleen, who doesn't seem to have any hostility, is roasting a mouse
over the fire...
Oh, thank you very much. It's a kind offer, but...I'll decline.

There are many signs from this floor... It seems that there are quite
a number of Floslins.
……There is a possibility that a large tribe has taken root. Be careful.

With this many signs, it wouldn't be strange if there were high-level
chieftains here. Let's brace ourselves and keep going.
Enicia and the others proceed forward while increasing their tension.
